And so that's what's going off
out here.

00:12:40.418 --> 00:12:45.350
And this is coming off of every
level here.

00:12:45.350 --> 00:12:46.279
Okay?
 

00:12:46.279 --> 00:12:50.832
So you can think of this as
what's left over and this is the

00:12:50.832 --> 00:12:55.309
flow of all that ATP driven
stuff on the planet surface.

00:12:58.309 --> 00:13:00.120
Now how does that look in space?
 

00:13:00.120 --> 00:13:05.235
Well if you look at tons of
carbon fixed per hectare per

00:13:05.235 --> 00:13:09.086
year,
where green is a lot and yellow

00:13:09.086 --> 00:13:13.288
is a little,
you can see that the forests

00:13:13.288 --> 00:13:15.490
are really important.
 

00:13:15.490 --> 00:13:17.330
Okay?
 

00:13:17.330 --> 00:13:21.376
And the closer you get to the
equator and the wetter it gets,

00:13:21.376 --> 00:13:25.019
the more efficient the forests
are at fixing carbon.

00:13:25.019 --> 00:13:28.250
This is for the terrestrial
part of the world.

00:13:28.250 --> 00:13:33.226
If you could put the reefs in,
they would be fixing carbon,

00:13:33.226 --> 00:13:37.857
and they would be withdrawing
it on kind of a different

00:13:37.857 --> 00:13:39.058
timescale.
 

